#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:128
msgid "Evaluates referring domains, backlink quality, anchor text distribution, and domain authority to improve site credibility and search rankings."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:129
msgid "Validates keyword selection, analyzes competition metrics, and prevents cannibalization across content."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:130
msgid "Analyzes content readability and tone to ensure it matches the target audience`s expectations. Provides recommendations for adjustments to improve audience targeting."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:131
msgid "Scans page content to extract and evaluate internal and external links. Checks link status via internal or external service, returning details about broken or redirecting URLs to maintain healthy backlinks."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:132
msgid "Verifies that canonical tags are present and correctly point to the preferred URL. Ensures proper formatting to avoid duplicate content issues and guides updates when canonical references are missing or incorrect."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:133
msgid "Validates the depth and comprehensiveness of content by analyzing subtopic coverage, semantic richness, and user intent satisfaction. Provides suggestions for improving content quality based on analysis results."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:134
msgid "Validates content formatting for headings, paragraphs, and bullet points to ensure readability and SEO best practices."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:135
msgid "Validates the content length of a post against predefined benchmarks. Analyzes word count, structure, and provides suggestions for optimization."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:136
msgid "Analyzes and optimizes content for SEO by focusing on keyword usage, content quality, readability, and meta tags."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:137
msgid "Evaluates content length, depth, readability, and multimedia inclusion to enhance overall content quality and user engagement."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:138
msgid "Checks how easy the content is to read, how it is structured, and whether it suits the intended audience to improve engagement and clarity."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:139
msgid "Analyzes content age and relevance to suggest updates or pruning. Reviews industry trends and competitor changes, generating actionable recommendations for refreshing outdated sections or removing obsolete information to maintain quality."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:140
msgid "Ensures canonical tags referencing external domains are used correctly when content is syndicated. Validates host consistency and suggests adjustments so search engines attribute authority to the original source."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:141
msgid "Checks meta description for excessive repetition of target keywords. Calculates optimal ratio between primary and secondary terms, flagging when overuse occurs to prevent penalties from keyword stuffing."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:142
msgid "Analyzes the quality of image alt text on a page, ensuring it is descriptive and useful for SEO and accessibility. Flags poor alt text (e.g., filenames) as needing improvement."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:143
msgid "Detects duplicate pages within the site and reviews canonical tags to ensure proper consolidation. Uses simulated API results to minimize load and caches findings, guiding resolution of content redundancy."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:144
msgid "Checks if the primary keyword is used in the first paragraph of the content. This is important for SEO as it helps search engines understand the main topic of the page early on."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:145
msgid "Detects keyword stuffing in the first paragraph and computes language-agnostic distribution metrics for repetition and proximity. This is crucial for maintaining readability and avoiding penalties from search engines."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:146
msgid "Evaluates keyword placement, density, and engagement in opening paragraphs to optimize topic relevance and reader connection."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:147
msgid "Identifies broken internal and external links, prioritizing critical issues affecting user experience and SEO performance. If no links are found on the page, this check is marked as passed by default."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:148
msgid "Evaluates header tag order and structure to ensure consistent hierarchy. Checks for single H1, avoiding jumps or improper resets, and provides suggestions to improve heading organization for better readability and SEO."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:149
msgid "Queries external APIs to confirm whether a page is indexed by Google and Bing. Reports indexation status and provides guidance on improving visibility if the URL is missing from search results."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:150
msgid "Analyzes page headings to verify proper hierarchical structure, single H1 usage, and no missing levels. Computes a score based on nesting consistency and heading quality, offering guidance to improve SEO-friendly headers."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:151
msgid "Analyzes HTML heading tags (h1-h6) hierarchy, keyword usage, and structural consistency to enhance content organization and SEO effectiveness."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:152
msgid "Examines page URLs to ensure words are separated with hyphens rather than underscores. Detects any underscores and offers guidance to standardize URL structure, improving readability and search engine recognition."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:153
msgid "Checks images for excessive file sizes, assessing compression efficiency. Calculates average size and identifies any files above a set threshold, advising compression improvements to speed up page load and enhance SEO."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:154
msgid "Evaluates how images are compressed, formatted, and scaled responsively to reduce load times and improve usability across devices. If no images are found on the page, this check is marked as passed by default."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:155
msgid "Analyzes keyword competition, search volume, and CPC balance using external SEO API services. Provides insights on keyword difficulty and potential for content optimization."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:156
msgid "Calculates keyword density across the page to detect excessive or insufficient usage. Evaluates primary and secondary terms, suggesting adjustments to keep frequencies within recommended ranges for natural, SEO-friendly content."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:157
msgid "Assesses how keywords are spread throughout page headings, paragraphs, and meta data. Identifies imbalances like concentration in specific sections and recommends a more even distribution for improved relevance."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:158
msgid "Performs keyword mapping analysis across site content, detecting cannibalization and coverage issues."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:159
msgid "Examines heading elements for primary and secondary keyword usage, measuring frequency and placement. Highlights overuse or absence of keywords in headers to improve relevancy and SEO performance."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:160
msgid "Analyzes and optimizes internal and external linking strategies to enhance site authority and user navigation."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:161
msgid "Checks if local keywords appear in meta titles, descriptions, and image alt text to strengthen local SEO signals. Calculates coverage percentages and suggests improvements when location-specific phrases are missing."
msgstr ""

#: app/src/Domain/Integrations/WordPress/Seo/Entities/Optimiser/Base/Attributes/SeoMeta.php:162
msgid "Analyzes titles, headings, and body text for location-specific keywords to evaluate local SEO strength. Measures keyword distribution across content elements and highlights gaps where local terms could be incorporated."
